# Privacy Policy for Flash

Effective Date: May 11, 2025

Flash ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is collected, used, and disclosed by our mobile application Flash.

## 1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:
- Device information (e.g., device model, OS version)
- Usage data (e.g., screens viewed, time spent in-app)
- Crash logs (for improving app stability)

We do not collect personal identifying information such as names, emails, or contacts.

## 2. How We Use Information
We use the collected information solely to:
- Improve app performance and usability
- Fix crashes and bugs
- Understand general usage patterns

## 3. Data Sharing
We do not share your data with third parties. Data is only used internally for improving the app.

## 4. Data Security
All data collected is transmitted securely and stored using encryption methods provided by Firebase and other services used by the app.

## 5. User Control and Data Deletion
As the app does not require login or account creation, personal user data is not stored. Users can uninstall the app at any time to delete all locally stored data.

## 6. Children's Privacy
Flash is intended for users aged 13 and above. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.

## 7. Contact Us
If you have any questions, contact us at: cortexdigitaltech@gmail.com
